Codex Chat Log - ESP32 Instrument Cluster

Request:
- Use ESP32_KITT_Display/code.py as a reference.
- Create a separate ESP32 version that represents an instrument cluster with gauges and idiot lights.
- Prefer a digital-first cluster layout.

Decisions:
- New folder: ESP32_Instrument_Cluster/
- Main app file: code.py
- Existing ESP32_KITT_Display/code.py remains untouched.
- Display layout: landscape 320x240 ST7789.
- Main screen priority: speed and RPM first.
- Visual style: clean OEM dark theme.
- Page button behavior: cluster page plus diagnostic pages.
- MPH calibration: VSS_PULSES_PER_MILE = 4000.
- Odometer display: bottom-center digital readout.

Odometer behavior:
- Odometer starts at 0 unless a saved file exists.
- Odometer state is stored in /odometer.json.
- Saved state uses integer fields:
  - tenths: total completed 0.1-mile increments.
  - remainder_pulses: VSS pulse count since the last completed 0.1 mile.
- On startup, the app resumes from both saved values.
- With 4000 VSS pulses per mile, 400 pulses equal one 0.1-mile increment.
- The app saves periodically while tach is active.
- The app also saves once when tach becomes stale, treating that as engine shutdown.
- Odometer helpers are structured so file storage can later be replaced with FRAM.

